  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
	Suppose that
	<me>
	  A = \begin{bmatrix}
	  2.1 \amp -1.9 \amp 0.1 \amp 3.7 \\
	  -1.5 \amp 2.7 \amp 0.9 \amp -0.6 \\
	  -0.4 \amp 2.8 \amp -1.5 \amp 4.2 \\
	  -0.4 \amp 2.4 \amp 1.9 \amp -1.8
	  \end{bmatrix}.
	</me>
	<sage>
	  <input>
	  </input>
	</sage>
	<ol marker="a.">
	  <li>
	    <p>
	      Find the singular values of <m>A</m>.  What is
	      <m>\rank(A)</m>? 
