    </statement>

    <solution>
      <p>
	<ol marker="a.">
	  <li>
	    <p>
	      The singular values <m>\sigma_i</m> are <m>45.5</m>, <m>32.6</m>,
	      <m>28.9</m>, and <m>15.9</m>.  Therefore, the variances
	      in the direction of the principal components are
	      given by <m>\frac{1}{1057}\sigma_i^2</m> and are
